  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "The initial output from LLMs typically exhibits low usability; for instance, studies report raw executability rates as low as 24% [99] and pass rates of merely 34% [89].",
    "However, this iterative validation-feedback-refinement cycle has been empirically proven to elevate effective pass rates to over 70% [56,99].",
    "Concurrently, some studies employ more lightweight, rule-based repair to effectively address common, pattern-based errors [124].",
    "The repair process itself can be quite sophisticated; for example, TestART [56] adopts a template-based repair mechanism, tailoring specific repair schemes for common error patterns, such as one template for missing imports and another for incorrect assertion statements.",
    "This targeted approach is highly effective, raising the test pass rate to 78.55%, significantly higher than the approximately 60% achieved by baseline implementations like ChatUniTest."
  ],
